[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm using <code>match</code> but Lean adds more stuff to the expression:</p>\n<p>For</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>the goal becomes</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Why did <code>h</code> get inserted into the <code>match</code>?</p>\n<p>For </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>the goal becomes</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">b1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">⊢</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Why did <code>b2</code> get inserted into the <code>match</code>?</p>\n<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 529603047,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1752947330
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well, you can do the following:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">generalizing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But why you use a value of type <code>Bool</code> like a type? It's not a type.</p>",
        "id": 529605998,
        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1752950814
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For the first one, the reason <code>h</code> gets inserted is so you have access to <code>h</code> with <code>b</code> substituted and in particular the second alternative becomes a contradiction:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/--</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">error: don't know how to synthesize placeholder</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">context:</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">b : Bool</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">h : false = true</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">⊢ Prop</span>\n\n<span class=\"sd\">Note: All holes (e.g., `_`) in the header of a theorem are resolved before the proof is processed; information from the proof cannot be used to infer what these values should be</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">guard_msgs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This way, you can also remove the second alternative because the <code>match</code> gets to know <code>h</code>.</p>",
        "id": 529609954,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1752955811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The second one is probably some weird edge case idk</p>",
        "id": 529609969,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1752955831
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the reasons are:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>substituting values in the local context</li>\n<li>finding contradictions using hypotheses from the local context</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 529610043,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1752955944
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"394485\">suhr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/.60match.60.20expression.20adds.20additional.20expressions/near/529605998\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But why you use a value of type <code>Bool</code> like a type? It's not a type.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What do you mean? Where am I doing that? Is <code>match</code> only for types?</p>",
        "id": 529612644,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1752959262
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"933054\">Snir</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/.60match.60.20expression.20adds.20additional.20expressions/near/529603047\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Notice the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>b : Bool</code></li>\n<li><code>match b with ... : Bool</code>, because each branch is <code>b</code></li>\n<li>So you use a value of type <code>Bool</code> as type of the result</li>\n<li>But <code>Bool</code> is not a type universe</li>\n<li>Therefore, a value of type <code>Bool</code> is not a type</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 529612860,
        "sender_full_name": "suhr",
        "timestamp": 1752959543
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"933054\">Snir</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/.60match.60.20expression.20adds.20additional.20expressions/near/529612644\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"394485\">suhr</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/.60match.60.20expression.20adds.20additional.20expressions/near/529605998\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But why you use a value of type <code>Bool</code> like a type? It's not a type.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What do you mean? Where am I doing that? Is <code>match</code> only for types?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Your original message is</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>here after the main colon, you have a match statement that produces <code>b</code>, so without that statement your code would look like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">true</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>By putting the <code>b</code> after the colon you are treating it as a type, so essentially <code>foo</code> will have type <code>b</code>.</p>",
        "id": 529612874,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1752959559
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, <code>Bool</code> is automatically coerced to <code>Prop</code>, you can see that in the generated goal.<br>\nThe <code>b</code> in each branch of the <code>match</code> gets converted to the proposition <code>b = true</code>.<br>\nThe same is true for <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110064\">@Kenny Lau</span>'s second example</p>",
        "id": 529613720,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1752960706
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I understand the <code>generalizing</code> thing with <code>h</code>, thanks!<br>\nWith <code>b1 b2</code>, do you know what's going on?<br>\nI also noticed that it has something to do with the type-checker, since explicitly specifying the type of <code>b2</code> removes it from the <code>match</code>.</p>",
        "id": 529614649,
        "sender_full_name": "Snir Broshi",
        "timestamp": 1752961981
    }
]